	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Hi,
<br />
<br />I'm very new here, but I was in the same position as you just a month or two ago. I knew a small amount about soldering, but that was about it. From reading and posting, I've completed NROM, CNROM, UNROM and TSROM devcarts.. and I can play quite a large number of games / demos.
<br />
<br />As far as opening the SMB3 cart, look here:
<br />
<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.raphnet.net/electronique/nes_mod/nes_mod_en.php#cartridge_cleaning">http://www.raphnet.net/electronique/nes ... e_cleaning</a><!-- m -->
<br />
<br />The guy on that page recommends heating up a small piece of plastic, and inserting it into the hole so it will mold to the screw... and that seems like a good idea. You could also search for "nes gamebit" on eBay. I found a  gamebit to open NES games for about US$3.
<br />
<br />It was easy to make the NROM / CNROM devcats - no rewiring needed! Try them out first to get the hang of things - that's what I did before I moved on the UNROM, and finally the mapper 3 TSROM cart - which required cut traces and quite a few rewired points.
<br />
<br />As for an EPROM programmer, I bought a Willem from <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.sivava.com/">http://www.sivava.com/</a><!-- m --> They shipped quick and it works well. I bought flash roms from eBay, and EPROMS from Jameco. I also recommend getting some sockets, so it is easier to take the rom's in and out. I got ZIF sockets because they really do require no force to remove (and I was surprised how easy it was to bend the pins).
<br />
<br />If you have any other questions - let me know. I'll be happy to help with what I know (so far)...
<br />
<br />NC

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


