	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />It looks like that programmer supports many of the chips needed for NESdev, but it seems a bit expensive (isn't it like US$95?). It also looks like it doesn't have the ZIF socket connection for the DIP connections, so it might be nice to put one in (to make it easier to get chips in and out).
<br />
<br />The screenshot for the software looks very similar to the Willem programmer software.. which is easy to use and well-documented on the CD that comes with the programmer. But who knows about support / forums for the programmer in the auction?
<br />
<br />Hmm.. I do a lot of record trading to Brazil, and I sometimes have friends who travel back and forth. I can see if anyone is going soon. Perhaps they can take a programmer to Brazil, and then send it to you when they arrive. I do that all the time to get around the cost of customs. If I send packages from the USA - they always charge extra because of where it is coming from!
<br />
<br />NROM / CNROM carts don't need to be rewired because the pinouts on those EPROM's match the original chips that Nintendo used when they made the game.
<br />
<br />Compare these two pinouts:
<br />
<br />Look at the first one - PRG ROM - 32KBytes (28pin)
<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://nesdev.com/NES%20ROM%20Pinouts.txt">http://nesdev.com/NES%20ROM%20Pinouts.txt</a><!-- m -->
<br />
<br />Now look at this pinout for a common EPROM (27C256):
<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://jameco.com/wcsstore/Jameco/Products/ProdDS/39714.pdf">https://jameco.com/wcsstore/Jameco/Prod ... /39714.pdf</a><!-- m -->
<br />
<br />You'll notice that the pins match on the original Nintendo rom and the EPROM <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" />
<br />
<br />It's when the pinouts don't match that it gets tricky. Rewiring, cutting traces, and burning your fingers... that's what I've been doing a lot of lately - but I'm getting the hang of it <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" />
<br />
<br />Hope that helps.
<br />
<br />NC

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


