		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I made this EPROM programmer which was quick and not too hard to solder if you take your time. It just costs a few bucks to make.
<br />
<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.zws.com/products/epromr2/epromr_stage1.html">http://www.zws.com/products/epromr2/epromr_stage1.html</a><!-- m -->
<br />
<br />It uses a PC parallel port and works for all the NES type EPROM's. The software is on the website and works very well. I keep an old PC in the basement just for EPROM and cellphone programming.

		

