		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">tokumaru wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><div class="quotetitle">No Carrier wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Actually, a ZIF or regular DIP socket will allow you to easily take chips in and out of the board. You don't have to solder them in every time.</div><br />So I can just install one of those on the cart? Wouldn't it be too bulky to fit on the console?<br /></div>
<br />
<br />Yes, you'll have to take the metal bar that goes across the slot where the cart goes in (on a front-loading NES). You'll also have to cut a hole in the cart itself, because it will be too high to fit in the case.
<br />
<br />Look here:
<br />
<br /><a href="http://www.54.org/condev/NESMods/NESMods_Remove_Metal_Piece.jpg" class="postlink">http://www.54.org/condev/NESMods/NESMods_Remove_Metal_Piece.jpg</a>
<br />
<br />and here:
<br />
<br /><a href="http://i30.photobucket.com/albums/c325/chimyfolkbutter/NES%20Development/PopeyeDevelopmentCart.jpg" class="postlink">http://i30.photobucket.com/albums/c325/chimyfolkbutter/NES%20Development/PopeyeDevelopmentCart.jpg</a>
<br />
<br />I removed the metal bar, and I leave the top of one of my NES's unscrewed. I don't bother putting the cases on the games - I just put them directly into the NES.

		

